defs.docs:
GilRs - Game Input Library for Rust
 ===================================

defs.name: Gilrs
defs.docs: Main object responsible of managing gamepads.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates new `Gilrs` with default settings. See [`GilrsBuilder`](struct.GilrsBuilder.html)
 for more details.

defs.name: next_event
defs.docs: Returns next pending event.

defs.name: update
defs.docs: Updates internal state according to `event`.

defs.name: inc
defs.docs:
Increases internal counter by one. Counter data is stored with state and can be used to
 determine when last event happened. You probably want to use this function in your update
 loop after processing events.

defs.name: counter
defs.docs:
Returns counter. Counter data is stored with state and can be used to determine when last
 event happened.

defs.name: reset_counter
defs.docs: Sets counter to 0.

defs.name: gamepad
defs.docs:
Returns handle to gamepad with given ID. Unlike `connected_gamepad()`, this function will
 also return handle to gamepad that is currently disconnected.

defs.name: connected_gamepad
defs.docs: Returns a reference to connected gamepad or `None`.

defs.name: gamepads
defs.docs: Returns iterator over all connected gamepads and their ids.

defs.name: insert_event
defs.docs: Adds `ev` at the end of internal event queue. It can later be retrieved with `next_event()`.

defs.name: set_mapping
defs.value: fn <'b, O> (&mut self, gamepad_id: usize, mapping: &MappingData, name: O) -> Result<String, MappingError>
defs.docs:
Sets gamepad's mapping and returns SDL2 representation of them. Returned mappings may not be
 compatible with SDL2 - if it is important, use
 [`set_mapping_strict()`](#method.set_mapping_strict).

defs.name: set_mapping_strict
defs.value: fn <'b, O> (&mut self, gamepad_id: usize, mapping: &MappingData, name: O) -> Result<String, MappingError>
defs.docs:
Similar to [`set_mapping()`](#method.set_mapping) but returned string should be compatible
 with SDL2.

defs.name: GilrsBuilder
defs.docs: Allow to create `Gilrs ` with customized behaviour.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create builder with default settings. Use `build()` to create `Gilrs`.

defs.name: with_default_filters
defs.docs:
If `true`, use [`axis_dpad_to_button`](ev/filter/fn.axis_dpad_to_button.html),
 [`Jitter`](ev/filter/struct.Jitter.html) and [`deadzone`](ev/filter/fn.deadzone.html)
 filters with default parameters. Defaults to `true`.

defs.name: add_mappings
defs.docs: Adds SDL mappings.

defs.name: add_env_mappings
defs.docs:
If true, will add SDL mappings from `SDL_GAMECONTROLLERCONFIG` environment variable.
 Defaults to true.

defs.name: add_included_mappings
defs.docs:
If true, will add SDL mappings included from
 https://github.com/gabomdq/SDL_GameControllerDB. Defaults to true.

defs.name: set_axis_to_btn
defs.value: fn (mut self, pressed: f32, released: f32) -> Self
defs.docs:
Sets values on which `ButtonPressed` and `ButtonReleased` events will be emitted. `build()`
 will return error if `pressed ≤ released` or if one of values is outside [0.0, 1.0].

defs.name: set_update_state
defs.docs:
Disable or enable automatic state updates. You should use this if you use custom filters;
 in this case you have to update state manually anyway.

defs.name: build
defs.docs: Creates `Gilrs`.

defs.name: ConnectedGamepadsIterator
defs.docs: Iterator over all connected gamepads.

defs.name: Gamepad
defs.docs: Represents handle to game controller.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: Returns the mapping name if it exists otherwise returns the os provided name.

defs.name: map_name
defs.docs:
if `mapping_source()` is `SdlMappings` returns the name of the mapping used by the gamepad.
 Otherwise returns `None`.

defs.name: os_name
defs.docs: Returns the name of the gamepad supplied by the OS.

defs.name: uuid
defs.docs: Returns gamepad's UUID.

defs.name: state
defs.docs: Returns cached gamepad state.

defs.name: is_connected
defs.docs: Returns true if gamepad is connected.

defs.name: is_pressed
defs.docs:
Examines cached gamepad state to check if given button is pressed. Panics if `btn` is
 `Unknown`.

defs.name: value
defs.docs: Examines cached gamepad state to check axis's value. Panics if `axis` is `Unknown`.

defs.name: button_data
defs.docs: Returns button state and when it changed.

defs.name: axis_data
defs.docs: Returns axis state and when it changed.

defs.name: power_info
defs.docs: Returns device's power supply state. See [`PowerInfo`](enum.PowerInfo.html) for details.

defs.name: mapping_source
defs.docs:
Returns source of gamepad mapping. Can be used to filter gamepads which do not provide
 unified controller layout.

defs.name: is_ff_supported
defs.docs: Returns true if force feedback is supported by device.

defs.name: set_listener_position
defs.docs: Change gamepad position used by force feedback effects.

defs.name: axis_or_btn_name
defs.docs: Returns `AxisOrBtn` mapped to `Code`.

defs.name: button_code
defs.docs: Returns `Code` associated with `btn`.

defs.name: axis_code
defs.docs: Returns `Code` associated with `axis`.

defs.name: deadzone
defs.docs: Returns area in which axis events should be ignored.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: Returns ID of gamepad.

defs.name: SdlMappings
defs.docs: Gamepad uses SDL mappings.

defs.name: Driver
defs.docs: Gamepad does not use any mappings but driver should provide unified controller layout.

defs.name: None
defs.docs:
Gamepad does not use any mappings and most gamepad events will probably be `Button::Unknown`
 or `Axis::Unknown`

defs.name: MappingSource
defs.docs: Source of gamepad mappings.

defs.name: GamepadId
defs.docs: Gamepad ID.

defs.name: NotImplemented
defs.docs:
Gilrs does not support current platform, but you can use dummy context from this error if
 gamepad input is not essential.

defs.name: InvalidAxisToBtn
defs.docs: Either `pressed ≤ released` or one of values is outside [0.0, 1.0] range.

defs.name: Other
defs.docs: Platform specific error.

defs.name: Error
defs.docs: Error type which can be returned when creating `Gilrs`.

defs.name: MappingData
defs.docs: Stores data used to map gamepad buttons and axes.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates new `Mapping`.

defs.name: button
defs.docs: Returns `EvCode` associated with button index.

defs.name: axis
defs.docs: Returns `EvCode` associated with axis index.

defs.name: insert_btn
defs.value: fn (&mut self, from: ev::Code, to: Button) -> Option<ev::Code>
defs.docs: Inserts new button mapping.

defs.name: insert_axis
defs.value: fn (&mut self, from: ev::Code, to: Axis) -> Option<ev::Code>
defs.docs: Inserts new axis mapping.

defs.name: remove_button
defs.docs: Removes button and returns associated `NativEvCode`.

defs.name: remove_axis
defs.docs: Removes axis and returns associated `NativEvCode`.

defs.name: InvalidCode
defs.docs: Gamepad does not have element referenced by `EvCode`.

defs.name: InvalidName
defs.docs: Name contains comma (',').

defs.name: NotImplemented
defs.docs: This function is not implemented for current platform.

defs.name: NotConnected
defs.docs: Gamepad is not connected.

defs.name: DuplicatedEntry
defs.docs: Same gamepad element is referenced by axis and button.

defs.name: UnknownElement
defs.docs: `Mapping` with `Button::Unknown` or `Axis::Unknown`.

defs.name: NotSdl2Compatible
defs.docs: `Mapping` have button or axis that are not present in SDL2.

defs.name: MappingError
defs.value: MappingError::{InvalidCode, InvalidName, NotImplemented, NotConnected, DuplicatedEntry, UnknownElement, NotSdl2Compatible}
defs.docs: The error type for functions related to gamepad mapping.

defs.name: ev
defs.docs: Gamepad state and other event related functionality.

defs.name: filter
defs.docs: Alter events in various ways.

defs.name: Jitter
defs.docs: Discard axis events that changed less than `threshold`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates new `Repeat` filter with threshold set to 0.01.

defs.name: deadzone
defs.docs: Drops events in dead zone and remaps value to keep it in standard range.

defs.name: axis_dpad_to_button
defs.docs: Maps axis dpad events to button dpad events.

defs.name: Repeat
defs.docs: Repeats pressed keys.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates new `Repeat` filter with `after` set to 500ms and `every` set to 30ms.

defs.name: Filter
defs.docs: Allow filtering events.

defs.name: FilterFn
defs.docs: Actual filter implementation.

defs.name: filter
defs.value: fn (&self, ev: Option<Event>, gilrs: &mut Gilrs) -> Option<Event>

defs.name: GamepadState
defs.docs: Cached gamepad state.

defs.name: is_pressed
defs.docs:
Returns `true` if given button is pressed. Returns `false` if there is no information about
 `btn` or it is not pressed.

defs.name: value
defs.docs:
Returns value of `el` or 0.0 when there is no information about it. `el` can be either axis
 or button.

defs.name: buttons
defs.docs: Iterate over buttons data.

defs.name: axes
defs.docs: Iterate over axes data.

defs.name: button_data
defs.docs: Returns button state and when it changed.

defs.name: axis_data
defs.docs: Returns axis state and when it changed.

defs.name: ButtonDataIter
defs.docs: Iterator over `ButtonData`.

defs.name: AxisDataIter
defs.docs: Iterator over `AxisData`.

defs.name: ButtonData
defs.docs: Information about button stored in `State`.

defs.name: is_pressed
defs.docs: Returns `true` if button is pressed.

defs.name: value
defs.docs: Returns value of button.

defs.name: is_repeating
defs.docs: Returns `true` if button is repeating.

defs.name: counter
defs.docs: Returns value of counter when button state last changed.

defs.name: timestamp
defs.docs: Returns when button state last changed.

defs.name: AxisData
defs.docs: Information about axis stored in `State`.

defs.name: value
defs.docs: Returns value of axis.

defs.name: counter
defs.docs: Returns value of counter when axis value last changed.

defs.name: timestamp
defs.docs: Returns when axis value last changed.

defs.name: Code
defs.docs: Platform specific event code.

defs.name: Event
defs.docs: Holds information about gamepad event.

defs.name: id
defs.docs: Id of gamepad.

defs.name: event
defs.docs: Event's data.

defs.name: time
defs.docs: Time when event was emitted.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates new event with current time.

defs.name: drop
defs.docs: Returns `Event` with `EventType::Dropped`.

defs.name: is_dropped
defs.docs: Returns true if event is `Dropped` and should be ignored.

defs.name: ButtonPressed
defs.docs: Some button on gamepad has been pressed.

defs.name: ButtonRepeated
defs.docs: This event can be generated by [`ev::Repeat`](filter/struct.Repeat.html) event filter.

defs.name: ButtonReleased
defs.docs: Previously pressed button has been released.

defs.name: ButtonChanged
defs.docs: Value of button has changed. Value can be in range [0.0, 1.0].

defs.name: AxisChanged
defs.docs: Value of axis has changed. Value can be in range [-1.0, 1.0].

defs.name: Connected
defs.docs:
Gamepad has been connected. If gamepad's UUID doesn't match one of disconnected gamepads,
 newly connected gamepad will get new ID.

defs.name: Disconnected
defs.docs: Gamepad has been disconnected. Disconnected gamepad will not generate any new events.

defs.name: Dropped
defs.docs: There was an `Event`, but it was dropped by one of filters. You should ignore it.

defs.name: EventType
defs.value: EventType::{ButtonPressed, ButtonRepeated, ButtonReleased, ButtonChanged, AxisChanged, Connected, Disconnected, Dropped}
defs.docs: Gamepad event.

defs.name: Button
defs.value: Button::{South, East, North, West, C, Z, LeftTrigger, LeftTrigger2, RightTrigger, RightTrigger2, Select, Start, Mode, LeftThumb, RightThumb, DPadUp, DPadDown, DPadLeft, DPadRight, Unknown}
defs.docs: Gamepad's elements which state can be represented by value from 0.0 to 1.0.

defs.name: Axis
defs.value: Axis::{LeftStickX, LeftStickY, LeftZ, RightStickX, RightStickY, RightZ, DPadX, DPadY, Unknown}
defs.docs: Gamepad's elements which state can be represented by value from -1.0 to 1.0.

defs.name: is_stick
defs.docs: Returns true if axis is `LeftStickX`, `LeftStickY`, `RightStickX` or `RightStickY`.

defs.name: second_axis
defs.docs: Returns the other axis from same element of gamepad, if any.

defs.name: AxisOrBtn
defs.docs: Represents `Axis` or `Button`.

defs.name: ff
defs.docs: Force feedback module.

defs.name: BaseEffectType
defs.docs: Kind of [`BaseEffect`](struct.BaseEffect.html).

defs.name: BaseEffect
defs.docs: Basic building block used to create more complex force feedback effects.

defs.name: kind
defs.docs: Type of base effect.

defs.name: scheduling
defs.docs: Defines playback duration and delays between each repetition.

defs.name: envelope
defs.docs: Basic attenuation function.

defs.name: Envelope
defs.docs: Envelope shaped attenuation(time) function.

defs.name: Replay
defs.docs: Defines scheduling of the basic force feedback effect.

defs.name: after
defs.docs: Start playback `after` ticks after `Effect::play()` is called.

defs.name: play_for
defs.docs: Playback duration.

defs.name: with_delay
defs.docs: If playback should be repeated delay it for `with_delay` ticks.

defs.name: dur
defs.docs: Returns duration of effect calculated as `play_for + with_delay`.

defs.name: None
defs.docs: Effect is not attenuated by distance.

defs.name: Linear
defs.docs: Linear distance model.

defs.name: LinearClamped
defs.docs: Linear distance clamped model.

defs.name: Inverse
defs.docs: Inverse distance model.

defs.name: InverseClamped
defs.docs: Inverse distance clamped model.

defs.name: Exponential
defs.docs: Exponential distance model.

defs.name: ExponentialClamped
defs.docs: Exponential distance clamped model.

defs.name: DistanceModel
defs.value: DistanceModel::{None, Linear, LinearClamped, Inverse, InverseClamped, Exponential, ExponentialClamped}
defs.docs: Specifies how distance between effect source and listener attenuates effect.

defs.name: InvalidReferenceDistance
defs.docs: Reference distance is < 0.

defs.name: InvalidRolloffFactor
defs.docs: Rolloff factor is < 0.

defs.name: InvalidMaxDistance
defs.docs: Max distance is < 0.

defs.name: InvalidModelParameter
defs.docs: Possible divide by zero

defs.name: DistanceModelError
defs.docs:
Error that can be returned when passing [`DistanceModel`](struct.DistanceModel.html) with
 invalid value.

defs.name: Ticks
defs.docs: Represents duration.

defs.name: Infinitely
defs.docs: Play effect until stop() is called.

defs.name: For
defs.docs: Play effect for specified time.

defs.name: Repeat
defs.docs: Describes how long effect should be played.

defs.name: Effect
defs.docs: Handle to force feedback effect.

defs.name: play
defs.docs: Plays effect on all associated gamepads.

defs.name: set_gamepads
defs.docs:
Changes gamepads that are associated with effect. Effect will be only played on gamepads
 from last call to this function.

defs.name: add_gamepad
defs.docs: Adds gamepad to the list of gamepads associated with effect.

defs.name: set_repeat
defs.docs: Changes what should happen to effect when it ends.

defs.name: set_distance_model
defs.docs: Changes distance model associated with effect.

defs.name: set_position
defs.docs: Changes position of the source of effect.

defs.name: set_gain
defs.docs: Changes gain of the effect. `gain` will be clamped to \[0.0, f32::MAX\].

defs.name: EffectBuilder
defs.docs: Creates new [`Effect`](struct.Effect.html).

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates new builder with following defaults: no gamepads, no base effects, repeat set to
 infinitely, no distance model, position in (0.0, 0.0, 0.0) and gain 1.0. Use `finish()` to
 create new effect.

defs.name: add_effect
defs.docs: Adds new [`BaseEffect`](struct.BaseEffect.html).

defs.name: gamepads
defs.docs:
Changes gamepads that are associated with effect. Effect will be only played on gamepads
 from last call to this function.

defs.name: add_gamepad
defs.docs: Adds gamepad to the list of gamepads associated with effect.

defs.name: repeat
defs.docs: Changes what should happen to effect when it ends.

defs.name: distance_model
defs.docs: Changes distance model associated with effect.

defs.name: position
defs.docs: Changes position of the source of effect.

defs.name: gain
defs.docs: Changes gain of the effect. `gain` will be clamped to \[0.0, f32::MAX\].

defs.value: fn (&mut self, gilrs: &mut Gilrs) -> Result<Effect, Error>

defs.docs: Device is not connected

defs.name: InvalidDistanceModel
defs.docs: Distance model is invalid.

defs.name: SendFailed

defs.docs: Unexpected error has occurred
